race.comment: FIREBALL (4) resumes. Scored a tradesman like win over 1100m at Rosehill on debut after pulling away late. Returns with the one trial placing and J Mac can park him just off the speed with cover. Genuine top-three prospect who will be savaging the line. STAR OF JAMAICA (5) comes down from Queensland after saluting as fav at his second start over 1000m at the Sunshine Coast. Looking for this trip and has further upside. PROFITABELLE (18) just over a month between runs after making her debut with an eye-catching third over 1000m at this track. Kept up to the mark with a searching 1050m trial win at Randwick. Can race closer from the draw and has top-three prospects. WHERE'S THE CIRCUS (9) speedy filly who blew her more fancied rivals away on debut at the big odds over 1000m in the LR Inglis Nursery at this track. Finds a lot more pressure here and must be kept safe. SCREEN ICON (11) produced a solid set of figures on debut in the Gimcrack. Respect. The chances don't end there.
